<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-28T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-28T03:00:00-05:00" n="357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163/876: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-28T17:00:00+09:00">March 28, 1939—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 28—6:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>151. Department’s 76, March 27, 8 p.m., bombing of mission
                                properties. I do not see how any other conclusion is possible.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>